</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="31.[151,1437,764,935]" pageId="31" pageNumber="182">
The genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1876" box="[274,361,765,791]" class="Insecta" family="Phaneropteridae" genus="Melidia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="182" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[274,361,765,791]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="182">Melidia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
currently contains the 4 species 
<taxonomicName authority="Stal, 1876" authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1876" box="[726,985,764,791]" class="Insecta" family="Phaneropteridae" genus="Melidia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="182" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brunneri">
<emphasis box="[726,861,765,791]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="182">M. brunneri</emphasis>
Stål, 1876
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Massa, 2015" authorityName="Massa" authorityYear="2015" box="[996,1281,764,791]" class="Insecta" family="Phaneropteridae" genus="Melidia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="182" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="claudiae">
<emphasis box="[996,1129,765,791]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="182">M. claudiae</emphasis>
Massa, 2015
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Chopard, 1954" authorityName="Chopard" authorityYear="1954" class="Insecta" family="Phaneropteridae" genus="Melidia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="182" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kenyensis">
<emphasis box="[1292,1436,765,791]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="182">M. kenyensis</emphasis>
Chopard, 1954
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Chopard, 1954" authorityName="Chopard" authorityYear="1954" box="[377,695,800,827]" class="Insecta" family="Phaneropteridae" genus="Melidia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="182" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laminata">
<emphasis box="[377,516,801,827]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="182">M. laminata</emphasis>
Chopard, 1954
</taxonomicName>
. Species of the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Stal, 1876" authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1876" box="[951,1161,800,827]" class="Insecta" family="Phaneropteridae" genus="Melidia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="182" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[951,1038,801,827]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="182">Melidia</emphasis>
Stål, 1876
</taxonomicName>
are fully winged and in habitus typical 
<taxonomicName authorityName="H.Burmeister" authorityYear="1838" box="[325,511,837,863]" class="Insecta" family="Tettigoniidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="182" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Phaneropterinae">Phaneropterinae</taxonomicName>
. All species are predominantly green or yellowish-green and males have a brown patch in the stridulatory area. The species are distributed throughout eastern, central and southern Africa (
<bibRefCitation author="Ragge, D. R." pageId="31" pageNumber="182" pagination="67 - 192" refId="ref20287" refString="Ragge, D. R. (1980) A review of the African Phaneropterinae with open tympana (Orthoptera: Tettigoniidae). Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History), Entomology Series, 40, 67 - 192." type="journal article" year="1980">Ragge 1980</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
